      BEGIN DSSUBRECORD
         Name "MBRALTINFL"
         Description =+=+=+=
A flag denoting if a member has an alternate insurance carrier.
D=Dual Coverage: Indicates that all matching member records should
be considered to determine the most appropriate record to use for
adjudication. It also indicates that the current record is open for use to
pay claims. If a member record with this code is determined to be the
best match, then the claim is adjudicated against this record, and acts
as an N record from that point forward. This indicates that the record is
secondary coverage. (SR 10125)
N=No: Member does not have additional coverage. This indicates
primary coverage.
X=Y/Dual Coverage: Acts like Y. When the flag is X, the system
continues to look for other matching records to use. If another
matching record is found with a D, then the Dual Coverage logic is
used to determine which record to use for adjudication. If the only
available record is X, then the claim will reject. This indicates that the
record is secondary coverage. (SR 10125)
Y=Yes: Member has additional coverage that should be used instead
of the submitted insurance. The current claim will reject so that the
pharmacy can resubmit the claim with the alternate (primary)
insurance information. This indicates that the record is secondary
coverage.
0=Additional Coverage: There is additional coverage and RxCLAIM
should look under the same carrier for the benefits. This indicates that
the record is secondary coverage.
1=Additional Coverage, Other Carrier: There is additional coverage,
but RxCLAIM should look under another carrier for the benefits. This
indicates that the record is secondary coverage. SR 21617 added
functionality where you can set up the router control table to
automatically create the secondary COB claim upon submission of the
=+=+=+=
         SqlType "1"
         Precision "1"
         Scale "0"
         Nullable "1"
         KeyPosition "0"
         DisplaySize "0"
         Group "0"
         SortKey "0"
         SortType "0"
         TableDef "DB2/UDB\\OptumRX\\CLM"
         AllowCRLF "0"
         LevelNo "0"
         Occurs "0"
         PadNulls "0"
         SignOption "0"
         SortingOrder "0"
         ArrayHandling "0"
         SyncIndicator "0"
         PadChar ""
         ColumnReference "MBRALTINFL"
         ExtendedPrecision "0"
         TaggedSubrec "0"
         OccursVarying "0"
         PKeyIsCaseless "0"
         SCDPurpose "0"
      END DSSUBRECORD
